Blue-Green Deployment POC – Demo Notes 

Objective 

The objective of this POC was to implement a Blue-Green deployment strategy on Azure App Service using Azure DevOps pipelines, enabling zero-downtime deployments and easy rollback capabilities. 

Environment Setup 

Created an Azure App Service named BLUE-GREEN-DEPLOYMENT in demo-rg. Initially the App Service Plan did not support deployment slots. After identifying the limitation, the plan was upgraded to Standard S1 to enable deployment slot functionality. 

Source Code and Repository 

The application source code, deployment scripts, validation scripts, and Azure DevOps YAML pipeline were maintained in a Git repository. 

Azure DevOps Pipeline 

Implemented a multi-stage YAML pipeline: Build → DeployToStaging → Validation → SwapProduction. 

Initial Challenge 

The deployment initially failed because the pipeline attempted to deploy to a staging slot that did not exist. The App Service Plan did not support deployment slots. 

Resolution 

Upgraded the App Service Plan to Standard S1 and created a staging deployment slot by cloning production settings. 

Deployment Validation 

Successfully deployed the application to the staging slot and validated application availability and deployment health. 

Slot Swap 

Performed a slot swap to move the validated application from staging to production with zero downtime. 

Rollback Strategy 

Rollback can be achieved by swapping the slots again, restoring the previous version within seconds. 

Key Learnings 

Azure App Service, Deployment Slots, Azure DevOps YAML Pipelines, Blue-Green Deployment, Slot Swapping, Validation Automation, Zero-Downtime Deployment, and Rollback Strategies. 

Conclusion 

Successfully implemented an end-to-end Blue-Green deployment solution using Azure App Service and Azure DevOps, enabling safer releases, automated validation, rapid rollback, and zero-downtime deployments. 
